      "content": "but isn't it kind of a stretch to say sovereignty is just \"administrative state interests\"? like, a country can't really function or protect its own people if it doesn't have control over who enters. doesn't that make the border security argument just as much of a \"moral imperative\" for the people living there? it feels like you're saying one side is just about paperwork while the other is about actual human lives.",
